2500|$|Kharitonchiki (singular: kharitonchik [...] ) is {{an analog}} of trinitite found in Semipalatinsk Test Site in Kazakhstan at <b>ground</b> <b>zeroes</b> of Soviet {{atmospheric}} nuclear tests. Also generically called Kharitonchik. They are pieces of molten rock left at <b>ground</b> <b>zeroes</b> after Soviet atmospheric nuclear tests. This porous black material {{is named after}} one of the leading Russian nuclear weapons scientists, Yulii Borisovich Khariton.|$|R
